# Aby (project design)

- **Design system name:** Aby — follow `.cursor/skills/aby/SKILL.md` for typography, color, motion, layout, and visual detail.
- **Product spec:** Routes, content, CTAs, SEO, legal/business facts, and structure live in `.cursor/memory-bank/` (start with `projectbrief.md`, full detail in `PRD.md`).
- **Conflict resolution:** Keep PRD facts exact (phone numbers, addresses, hours, links). For look-and-feel (fonts, decoration, motion, composition), **Aby** wins over older boilerplate choices in the codebase or PRD font examples unless you are explicitly aligning a section to a documented brand token the client locked in.
- **Live UI vs Aby prose:** The shipped site uses **Neo Aurora** — cool ice/violet base, electric **cyan–fuchsia–violet** accents, frosted chrome panels, and a **high-opacity nav** (no hero type bleeding through). Primary CTA: **Book Free Appointment** → `/contact`. If the Aby skill suggests a different mood, treat **codebase tokens and components** as source of truth unless the user asks to realign.
- **Web Interface Guidelines:** Baseline a11y, focus, forms, motion (`prefers-reduced-motion`), touch/safe-area, and performance expectations follow **Vercel Web Interface Guidelines**, summarized in `.cursor/skills/aby/SKILL.md` § *Web Interface Guidelines (baseline compliance)*. Refetch [command.md](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/vercel-labs/web-interface-guidelines/main/command.md) when doing a full audit.

When the user attaches or references the Aby skill, treat it as the same standard as this rule.
